org.dice_research.squirrel.fetcher

Interface Fetcher

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DereferencingFetcher, DumpFetcher, FTPFetcher, HTTPFetcher, JsonFetcher, MicroServiceBasedCkanFetcher, PaginatedCkanFetcher, SimpleCkanFetcher, SimpleOrderedFetcherManager, SparqlBasedFetcher, SparqlDatasetFetcher

    public interface Fetcher
extends Closeable
    Interface of a class that fetches the data of a given CrawleableUri instance.
    Author:
    Michael Röder (michael.roeder@uni-paderborn.de)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default File fetch(org.dice_research.squirrel.data.uri.CrawleableUri uri)
      Fetches a stream of data from the given URI, stores it and returns a File object pointing to the stored data.
      File fetch(org.dice_research.squirrel.data.uri.CrawleableUri uri, Delayer delayer)
      Fetches a stream of data from the given URI by following the delay implemented by the given Delayer, stores it and returns a File object pointing to the stored data.

    • Method Detail

      • fetch

        default File fetch(org.dice_research.squirrel.data.uri.CrawleableUri uri)
            throws RuntimeException
        Fetches a stream of data from the given URI, stores it and returns a File object pointing to the stored data. If an error occurs, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        uri - The URI from which data should be fetched.
        Returns:
        A File object pointing to the downloaded data or null if an error occurred.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException

      • fetch

        File fetch(org.dice_research.squirrel.data.uri.CrawleableUri uri,
           Delayer delayer)
        Fetches a stream of data from the given URI by following the delay implemented by the given Delayer, stores it and returns a File object pointing to the stored data. If an error occurs, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        uri - The URI from which data should be fetched.
        Returns:
        A File object pointing to the downloaded data or null if an error occurred.
